---
import Shell from '../components/Shell.astro';
---

<Shell
  title="About Auriti Labs — GEO Optimizer & GeoReady"
  description="Auriti Labs builds open-source tools for AI search visibility. GEO Optimizer is the audit engine. GeoReady is the monitoring platform."
  canonical="https://geoready.dev/about/"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 md:py-16">
    <header class="mb-14 md:mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[10px] font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider">
        <span>GEO Optimizer</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-text-muted" />
        <span>About</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight tracking-tight">
        About Auriti Labs
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-4 text-base md:text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Auriti Labs builds open-source tools for AI search visibility and Generative Engine Optimization.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12">

      {/* Products */}
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">Products</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">

          <div class="p-6 rounded-[--radius-lg] border border-border bg-bg-surface">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-accent-teal mt-2 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">GEO Optimizer</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  Open-source Python toolkit for auditing AI search visibility. Scores websites across
                  8 signal categories — robots.txt, llms.txt, schema, meta tags, content, signals,
                  AI discovery, and brand entity. MIT licensed. Available as a CLI and as a web tool
                  at <a href="https://geoready.dev" class="text-accent-teal hover:underline">geoready.dev</a>.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-xs font-mono">
                  <a href="https://github.com/Auriti-Labs/geo-optimizer-skill" class="text-text-muted hover:text-accent-teal transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub →</a>
                  <a href="https://pypi.org/project/geo-optimizer-skill/" class="text-text-muted hover:text-accent-teal transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PyPI →</a>
                  <a href="https://auriti-labs.github.io/geo-optimizer-skill/" class="text-text-muted hover:text-accent-teal transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Docs →</a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-[--radius-lg] border border-border bg-bg-surface">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-accent-teal/50 mt-2 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">GeoReady <span class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted ml-1">Early access</span></h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  The commercial monitoring platform built on GEO Optimizer. Adds continuous score
                  tracking, regression alerts, score history, and team workflows for agencies and
                  developers managing multiple sites. Available at
                  <a href="https://app.geoready.dev" class="text-accent-teal hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">app.geoready.dev</a>.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 text-xs font-mono">
                  <a href="/pricing/" class="text-text-muted hover:text-accent-teal transition-colors">See plans →</a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Research foundation */}
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Research foundation</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The scoring methodology is grounded in peer-reviewed research on AI search retrieval:
          the Princeton KDD 2024 study on generative engine optimization and the AutoGEO ICLR 2026
          paper on automated GEO. Every signal in GEO Optimizer is traceable to a published source.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/research/" class="text-sm text-accent-teal hover:underline">Read the research foundation →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Open source */}
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Open source</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          GEO Optimizer is MIT licensed. The source code, scoring weights, audit methodology,
          and all 47 citability methods are publicly available on GitHub. The audit tool and CLI
          remain free with no rate limits.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="mt-4 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent-teal">
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary italic">
            AI visibility infrastructure should be auditable by anyone, not locked behind
            proprietary black boxes.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/manifesto/" class="text-sm text-accent-teal hover:underline">Read the manifesto →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Built in Italy */}
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Built in Italy. Designed for the global web.</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Auriti Labs is an independent software lab founded in Italy. GEO Optimizer and GeoReady
          are built to serve developers, SEO specialists, and content teams worldwide — regardless
          of language, market, or region. AI search engines operate globally; so does this toolkit.
        </p>
      </section>

      {/* Contact */}
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Bug reports and feature requests: <a href="https://github.com/Auriti-Labs/geo-optimizer-skill/issues" class="text-accent-teal hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Issues</a>.
          For everything else, reach out via GitHub.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "AboutPage",
    "name": "About Auriti Labs",
    "url": "https://geoready.dev/about/",
    "description": "Auriti Labs builds open-source tools for AI search visibility and Generative Engine Optimization. Products: GEO Optimizer (open-source audit engine) and GeoReady (commercial monitoring platform).",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Auriti Labs",
      "url": "https://geoready.dev"
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Auriti Labs",
      "url": "https://geoready.dev"
    },
    "mainEntity": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Auriti Labs",
      "url": "https://geoready.dev",
      "description": "Auriti Labs builds open-source tools for AI search visibility and Generative Engine Optimization.",
      "foundingDate": "2024",
      "foundingLocation": {
        "@type": "Country",
        "name": "Italy"
      },
      "areaServed": "Worldwide",
      "sameAs": [
        "https://github.com/Auriti-Labs",
        "https://pypi.org/project/geo-optimizer-skill/"
      ]
    }
  })} />
</Shell>
